{
  "book": 13,
  "chapter": 1,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "從亞當到亞伯拉罕"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創5‧1－32；10‧1－32；11‧10－26）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Adam, Seth, Enosh, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, Noah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Noah: Shem, Ham and Japheth. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshek and Tiras. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath and Togarmah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, the Kittites and the Rodanites. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put and Canaan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah and Sabteka. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Cush was the father of Nimrod, who became a mighty warrior on earth. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Egypt was the father of the Ludites, Anamites, Lehabites, Naphtuhites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Pathrusites, Kasluhites (from whom the Philistines came) and Caphtorites. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Canaan was the father of Sidon his firstborn, and of the Hittites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Jebusites, Amorites, Girgashites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Hivites, Arkites, Sinites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Arvadites, Zemarites and Hamathites. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Shem: Elam, Ashur, Arphaxad, Lud and Aram. The sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether and Meshek. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Arphaxad was the father of Shelah, and Shelah the father of Eber. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Two sons were born to Eber: One was named Peleg, because in his time the earth was divided; his brother was named Joktan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Joktan was the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Obal, Abimael, Sheba, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Ophir, Havilah and Jobab. All these were sons of Joktan. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Eber, Peleg, Reu, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Serug, Nahor, Terah "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "and Abram (that is, Abraham). "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以實瑪利的後裔"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創25‧12－16）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Abraham: Isaac and Ishmael. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "These were their descendants: Nebaioth the firstborn of Ishmael, Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Jetur, Naphish and Kedemah. These were the sons of Ishmael. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons born to Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan: Sheba and Dedan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanok, Abida and Eldaah. All these were descendants of Keturah. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以掃的後裔"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧1－19）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Abraham was the father of Isaac. The sons of Isaac: Esau and Israel. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 35,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam and Korah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 36,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam and Kenaz; by Timna: Amalek. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 37,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以東地的原住民"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧20－30）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 37,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 38,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer and Dishan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 39,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Lotan: Hori and Homam. Timna was Lotan’s sister. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 40,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho and Onam. The sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 41,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The son of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran and Keran. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 42,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan and Akan. The sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以東諸王"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧31－43）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 42,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 43,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "These were the kings who reigned in Edom before any Israelite king reigned: Bela son of Beor, whose city was named Dinhabah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 44,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah succeeded him as king. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 45,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites succeeded him as king. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 46,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, succeeded him as king. His city was named Avith. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 47,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah succeeded him as king. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 48,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth on the river succeeded him as king. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 49,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Shaul died, Baal-Hanan son of Akbor succeeded him as king. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 50,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When Baal-Hanan died, Hadad succeeded him as king. His city was named Pau, and his wife’s name was Mehetabel daughter of Matred, the daughter of Me-Zahab. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 50,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 51,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Hadad also died. The chiefs of Edom were: Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 52,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 53,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 54,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Magdiel and Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom. "
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}